    <section>
        <h2>Early Life</h2>
        <p>Virat Kohli was born on November 5, 1988, in Delhi, India. He started playing cricket at a very young age and quickly rose through the ranks due to his talent and determination. He was part of the Indian U-19 team that won the World Cup in 2008.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Cricket Career</h2>
        <p>Virat Kohli made his international debut in 2008 and has since become a key figure in Indian cricket. He has led the team to many memorable victories and holds numerous records in all formats of the game. His performances in matches like the 2016 T20 World Cup and 2018 tour of Australia are legendary.</p>
    </section>

